{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861533360,"sessionID":"ses_28667c40affeetVQib0KLqGTv4","part":{"id":"prt_d79988368001X4AEFo5z06L2OH","messageID":"msg_d79986379001pco7GRIN9nNKJU","sessionID":"ses_28667c40affeetVQib0KLqGTv4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-59b670c6963e4005b7d03689191a42a0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 Implementation Summary: PicoD JWT 中间件\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: Successfully implemented complete JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD module, providing secure session authentication for AgentCube platform API endpoints.\n5: \n6: ## Implementation Status: ✅ COMPLETE\n7: \n8: ## Components Implemented\n9: \n10: ### 1. Core Authentication (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n11: - **AuthManager struct**: RSA public key with thread-safe mutex\n12: - **NewAuthManager()**: Constructor that loads public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n13: - **ValidateToken()**: Token validation with RS256 algorithm, 1-minute clock skew tolerance\n14: - **AuthClaims struct**: Extends `jwt.RegisteredClaims` for standard JWT claims\n15: \n16: ### 2. Middleware Layer (`pkg/picod/middleware.go`)\n17: - **AuthMiddleware()**: Gin middleware function that:\n18:   - Extracts and validates Authorization header\n19:   - Enforces \"Bearer <token>\" format\n20:   - Validates JWT tokens using AuthManager\n21:   - Stores claims in Gin context\n22:   - Wraps request body with 32MB size limit\n23:   - Logs validation failures\n24: \n25: ### 3. Error Handling (`pkg/picod/errors.go`)\n26: Defined 6 authentication error constants:\n27: - `ErrMissingAuthHeader` → 401 Unauthorized\n28: - `ErrInvalidAuthFormat` → 401 Unauthorized\n29: - `ErrInvalidToken` → 401 Unauthorized\n30: - `ErrInvalidSignature` → 401 Unauthorized\n31: - `ErrTokenExpired` → 401 Unauthorized\n32: - `ErrInvalidPublicKey` → 500 Internal Server Error\n33: \n34: ### 4. Constants (`pkg/picod/constants.go`)\n35: - Environment variable: `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`\n36: - HTTP headers: `Authorization`\n37: - Error messages for all authentication error scenarios\n38: - Max body size: 32MB (32 << 20)\n39: \n40: ### 5. Server Integration (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n41: - Added `authManager` field to Server struct\n42: - AuthManager initialization in `NewServer()`\n43: - Route protection in `registerRoutes()`:\n44:   - `/api/*` routes require authentication\n45:   - `/health` endpoint remains public\n46: \n47: ### 6. Comprehensive Test Coverage\n48: \n49: #### Unit Tests (`pkg/picod/auth_test.go`)\n50: - ✅ AuthManager initialization (success and failure cases)\n51: - ✅ Public key validation (PEM format, RSA type, parsing errors)\n52: - ✅ Token validation (valid, invalid signature, expired, malformed)\n53: - ✅ Clock skew tolerance (1-minute leeway)\n54: \n55: #### Middleware Tests (`pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`)\n56: - ✅ Missing Authorization header\n57: - ✅ Invalid Authorization formats (Basic, Token, no prefix)\n58: - ✅ Valid token authentication\n59: - ✅ Invalid token formats\n60: - ✅ Expired token handling\n61: - ✅ Wrong signature detection\n62: - ✅ Wrong signing algorithm rejection (HS256)\n63: - ✅ Claims storage in context\n64: - ✅ Body size limit wrapping\n65: - ✅ Clock skew tolerance\n66: - ✅ Request abortion on errors\n67: \n68: #### Integration Tests (`pkg/picod/server_test.go`)\n69: - ✅ AuthManager initialization in Server\n70: - ✅ Protected route authentication\n71: - ✅ Public health endpoint access\n72: - ✅ Server startup with/without public key\n73: \n74: ## Security Features\n75: \n76: 1. **RSA Public Key Verification**: Strict validation at startup\n77: 2. **Signature Algorithm Enforcement**: Only RS256 accepted\n78: 3. **Clock Skew Tolerance**: 1-minute leeway for clock drift\n79: 4. **Request Size Limiting**: 32MB maximum body size\n80: 5. **Concurrent Safety**: Read-write mutex protects public key access\n81: 6. **Error Logging**: Warning-level logs for validation failures\n82: \n83: ## Test Results\n84: ```\n85: ✅ All tests passing\n86: - TestAuthMiddleware_ErrorCases: PASS\n87: - TestAuthMiddleware_ValidToken: PASS\n88: - TestAuthMiddleware_BodySizeWrapped: PASS\n89: - TestAuthMiddleware_ClockSkewTolerance: PASS\n90: - TestAuthMiddleware_RequestAbortedOnError: PASS\n91: - TestNewAuthManager: PASS\n92: - TestValidateToken: PASS\n93: - TestNewServer: PASS\n94: - TestHealthCheckHandler: PASS\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ## Code Quality\n98: - ✅ Zero compilation errors\n99: - ✅ Zero test failures\n100: - ✅ Follows Go best practices\n101: - ✅ Proper error handling throughout\n102: - ✅ Thread-safe implementation\n103: - ✅ Comprehensive documentation\n104: \n105: ## API Contracts Matched\n106: \n107: All requirements from delta-spec.md have been implemented:\n108: \n109: 1. ✅ AuthManager structure and methods\n110: 2. ✅ AuthMiddleware Gin middleware\n111: 3. ✅ Authorization header extraction and validation\n112: 4. ✅ Token verification integration\n113: 5. ✅ Error type definitions\n114: 6. ✅ HTTP status code mappings\n115: 7. ✅ Environment variable constants\n116: 8. ✅ HTTP header constants\n117: 9. ✅ Error message constants\n118: 10. ✅ Request size limit constants\n119: 11. ✅ Server structure extension\n120: 12. ✅ AuthManager initialization\n121: 13. ✅ Route protection\n122: 14. ✅ Error response format\n123: 15. ✅ Logging requirements\n124: 16. ✅ Security considerations\n125: 17. ✅ Concurrent safety\n126: 18. ✅ Test coverage requirements\n127: \n128: ## Files Modified/Created\n129: \n130: ### Created:\n131: - `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go` (344 lines) - Comprehensive middleware tests\n132: \n133: ### Already Existed (Verified Complete):\n134: - `pkg/picod/auth.go` - Core authentication logic\n135: - `pkg/picod/auth_test.go` - Auth unit tests\n136: - `pkg/picod/middleware.go` - Gin middleware\n137: - `pkg/picod/errors.go` - Error definitions\n138: - `pkg/picod/constants.go` - Constants\n139: - `pkg/picod/server.go` - Server integration\n140: - `pkg/picod/server_test.go` - Server integration tests\n141: \n142: ## Usage Example\n143: \n144: ```bash\n145: # Set public key environment variable\n146: export PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY=\"$(cat public_key.pem)\"\n147: \n148: # Start PicoD server\n149: ./picod\n150: \n151: # Access protected endpoint with JWT\n152: curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>\" http://localhost:8080/api/execute\n153: \n154: # Health check (public, no auth required)\n155: curl http://localhost:8080/health\n156: ```\n157: \n158: ## Conclusion\n159: \n160: The PicoD JWT middleware implementation is **COMPLETE** and **PRODUCTION-READY**. All requirements from AR-017 have been fully implemented with comprehensive test coverage, proper error handling, and security best practices.\n\n(End of file - total 160 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 Implementation Summary: PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n## Overview\nSuccessfully implemented complete JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD module, providing secure session authentication for AgentCube platform API endpoints.\n\n## Implementation Status: ✅ COMPLETE\n\n## Components Implemented\n\n### 1. Core Authentication (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n- **AuthManager struct**: RSA public key with thread-safe mutex\n- **NewAuthManager()**: Constructor that loads public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- **ValidateToken()**: Token validation with RS256 algorithm, 1-minute clock skew tolerance\n- **AuthClaims struct**: Extends `jwt.RegisteredClaims` for standard JWT claims\n\n### 2. Middleware Layer (`pkg/picod/middleware.go`)\n- **AuthMiddleware()**: Gin middleware function that:\n  - Extracts and validates Authorization header\n  - Enforces \"Bearer <token>\" format\n  - Validates JWT tokens using AuthManager","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775861533330,"end":1775861533359}}}}
