 format\n217: - [ ] Create test for valid token authentication\n218: - [ ] Create test for invalid token rejection\n219: - [ ] Create test for expired token rejection\n220: - [ ] Create test for body size limit application\n221: - [ ] Verify claims are stored in context after successful auth\n222: \n223: **Verification**: Review pkg/picod/middleware_test.go for AuthMiddleware tests\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ### Task 20: Add integration tests for authentication flow\n228: - [ ] Create test for public /health endpoint access\n229: - [ ] Create test for protected /api endpoint rejection without token\n230: - [ ] Create test for protected /api endpoint access with valid token\n231: - [ ] Create test for protected /api endpoint rejection with invalid token\n232: - [ ] Create test for complete request-response cycle\n233: - [ ] Verify test server setup and teardown\n234: \n235: **Verification**: Review pkg/picod/server_test.go for authentication integration tests\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ### Task 21: Add concurrent safety tests\n240: - [ ] Create test for concurrent token validations\n241: - [ ] Create test for concurrent middleware invocations\n242: - [ ] Verify no race conditions with go test -race\n243: - [ ] Verify read lock allows concurrent token validations\n244: - [ ] Verify mutex protects public key access\n245: \n246: **Verification**: Run `go test -race ./pkg/picod -run TestConcurrentAuth`\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Task 22: Verify logging implementation\n251: - [ ] Verify klog.Info() for successful AuthManager initialization\n252: - [ ] Verify klog.Warningf() for token validation failures\n253: - [ ] Verify no sensitive data is logged (public key, token content)\n254: - [ ] Verify log levels are appropriate (Info for startup, Warning for auth failures)\n255: \n256: **Verification**: Review pkg/picod/auth.go and middleware.go for logging statements\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ### Task 23: Verify security measures\n261: - [ ] Verify RS256 algorithm is enforced\n262: - [ ] Verify algorithm confusion prevention (explicit signing method check)\n263: - [ ] Verify token expiration is checked with leeway\n264: - [ ] Verify Authorization header is the only token source (no URL/body)\n265: - [ ] Verify error messages don't expose sensitive information\n266: - [ ] Verify body size limit is applied after authentication\n267: \n268: **Verification**: Review code against security considerations in design.md\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### Task 24: Run unit tests and verify coverage\n273: - [ ] Run `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestAuthManager -v`\n274: - [ ] Run `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestValidateToken -v`\n275: - [ ] Run `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestAuthMiddleware -v`\n276: - [ ] Run coverage analysis: `go test ./pkg/picod -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n277: - [ ] Verify coverage meets target (>80% for auth code)\n278: - [ ] Fix any failing tests or coverage gaps\n279: \n280: **Verification**: All tests pass with acceptable coverage\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ### Task 25: Run integration tests\n285: - [ ] Run `go test ./pkg/picod -run TestAuthenticationIntegration -v`\n286: - [ ] Verify public endpoint access works without token\n287: - [ ] Verify protected endpoint requires token\n288: - [ ] Verify valid token grants access\n289: - [ ] Verify invalid token is rejected\n290: - [ ] Verify error responses follow correct format\n291: \n292: **Verification**: All integration tests pass\n293: \n294: ---\n295: \n296: ### Task 26: Run race detector tests\n297: - [ ] Run `go test -race ./pkg/picod -run TestAuth`\n298: - [ ] Run `go test -race ./pkg/picod -run TestMiddleware`\n299: - [ ] Verify no race conditions detected\n300: - [ ] Fix any race condition issues found\n301: \n302: **Verification**: No race conditions detected\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ### Task 27: Verify static analysis passes\n307: - [ ] Run `go vet ./pkg/picod`\n308: - [ ] Fix any warnings or errors\n309: - [ ] Run `gofmt -s -w ./pkg/picod`\n310: - [ ] Verify code is properly formatted\n311: - [ ] Run linter if configured (golangci-lint)\n312: - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n313: \n314: **Verification**: Static analysis passes with no issues\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ### Task 28: Verify package builds successfully\n319: - [ ] Run `go build ./pkg/picod`\n320: - [ ] Verify package compiles without errors\n321: - [ ] Run `go build ./cmd/picod`\n322: - [ ] Verify CLI builds with auth functionality\n323: - [ ] Test binary with public key environment variable\n324: \n325: **Verification**: Package and CLI build successfully\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ### Task 29: Verify go.mod dependencies are correct\n330: - [ ] Verify github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0 is in dependencies\n331: - [ ] Verify github.com/gin-gonic/gin is present\n332: - [ ] Verify k8s.io/klog/v2 is present\n333: - [ ] Run `go mod tidy`\n334: - [ ] Run `go mod verify`\n335: - [ ] Verify all dependencies are resolved correctly\n336: \n337: **Verification**: Dependencies are correct and verified\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ### Task 30: Create test helper functions (if missing)\n342: - [ ] Create generateTestKeyPair() helper function\n343: - [ ] Create publicKeyToPEM() helper function\n344: - [ ] Create createTestToken() helper function\n345: - [ ] Create createExpiredToken() helper function\n346: - [ ] Verify helpers are exported or in test file as needed\n347: \n348: **Verification**: Test helpers exist and work correctly\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ### Task 31: Update CHANGE.md status\n353: - [ ] Open changes/AR-017/CHANGE.md\n354: - [ ] Update status to \"Completed\"\n355: - [ ] Add completion date\n356: - [ ] Add any implementation notes or deviations\n357: \n358: **Verification**: CHANGE.md reflects completion status\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ### Task 32: Update documentation\n363: - [ ] Update pkg/picod/README.md with JWT authentication section\n364: - [ ] Document PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY environment variable\n365: - [ ] Document Authorization header format\n366: - [ ] Document protected vs public endpoints\n367: - [ ] Add usage examples for authenticated requests\n368: - [ ] Document error responses for authentication failures\n369: - [ ] Add troubleshooting section for auth issues\n370: \n371: **Verification**: Documentation is complete and accurate\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ### Task 33: Add inline code comments (if needed)\n376: - [ ] Add comments to AuthManager struct explaining purpose\n377: - [ ] Add comments to ValidateToken explaining verification steps\n378: - [ ] Add comments to AuthMiddleware explaining flow\n379: - [ ] Ensure comments are concise and helpful\n380: - [ ] Verify no sensitive information in comments\n381: \n382: **Verification**: Code is well-commented\n383: \n384: ---\n385: \n386: ### Task 34: Verify design compliance\n387: - [ ] Cross-check implementation against design.md\n388: - [ ] Verify all data structures match\n389: - [ ] Verify all API contracts match\n390: - [ ] Verify error handling matches\n391: - [ ] Verify security measures are implemented\n392: - [ ] Document any deviations from design\n393: \n394: **Verification**: Implementation matches design specification\n395: \n396: ---\n397: \n398: ### Task 35: End-to-end verification test\n399: - [ ] Start PicoD server with test public key\n400: - [ ] Test /health endpoint without token (should succeed)\n401: - [ ] Test /api/execute without token (should fail 401)\n402: - [ ] Generate valid JWT test token\n403: - [ ] Test /api/execute with valid token (should succeed)\n404: - [ ] Test /api/files with valid token (should succeed)\n405: - [ ] Test with expired token (should fail 401)\n406: - [ Test with malformed token (should fail 401)\n407: - [ ] Stop server and verify graceful shutdown\n408: \n409: **Verification**: Complete end-to-end authentication flow works\n410: \n411: ---\n412: \n413: ### Task 36: Performance verification\n414: - [ ] Run benchmark tests for token validation\n415: - [ ] Measure validation latency (should be ~1-5ms)\n416: - [ ] Verify concurrent validation performance\n417: - [ ] Check memory usage for AuthManager\n418: - [ ] Verify no performance degradation with auth\n419: \n420: **Verification**: Performance meets design expectations\n421: \n422: ---\n423: \n424: ### Task 37: Final cleanup and review\n425: - [ ] Remove any temporary test files or data\n426: - [ ] Review all code for TODO comments\n427: - [ ] Review all code for debug statements\n428: - [ ] Ensure no hardcoded test values in production code\n429: - [ ] Verify all test files are named *_test.go\n430: - [ ] Verify no unused imports or variables\n431: \n432: **Verification**: Code is clean and production-ready\n433: \n434: ---\n435: \n436: ### Task 38: Create implementation summary\n437: - [ ] Document what was implemented\n438: - [ ] Document what was verified\n439: - [ ] Document any design decisions made\n440: - [ ] Document any deviations from design\n441: - [ ] Document known limitations or future work\n442: - [ ] Update changes/AR-017/README.md with summary\n443: \n444: **Verification**: Implementation summary is complete\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ## Summary\n449: \n450: **Total Tasks**: 38\n451: **Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 4-6 hours\n452: \n453: ### Key Deliverables\n454: 1. **Verified AuthManager implementation** - JWT authentication manager with RSA public key\n455: 2. **Verified AuthMiddleware implementation** - Gin middleware for request authentication\n456: 3. **Verified error handling** - Consistent error responses for auth failures\n457: 4. **Verified server integration** - Auth middleware applied to /api routes\n458: 5. **Unit tests** - Comprehensive tests for AuthManager and middleware\n459: 6. **Integration tests** - End-to-end authentication flow tests\n460: 7. **Documentation** - Updated documentation and usage examples\n461: 8. **Security verification** - Confirmed RS256, algorithm checking, expiration validation\n462: \n463: ### Success Criteria\n464: - All tasks completed successfully\n465: - All unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n466: - All integration tests pass\n467: - No race conditions detected\n468: - Static analysis passes with no warnings\n469: - Package and CLI build successfully\n470: - End-to-end authentication flow works correctly\n471: - Protected endpoints require valid JWT token\n472: - Public endpoints remain accessible\n473: - Error responses follow consistent format\n474: - Security measures are effective\n475: - Performance meets expectations\n476: - Documentation is complete and accurate\n477: \n478: ### Dependencies\n479: - Go 1.24+\n480: - github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0\n481: - github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n482: - k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n483: - github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0\n484: \n485: ### Blocked By\n486: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n487: \n488: ### Blocks\n489: - AR-009 (Router HTTP 反向代理核心) - Router may need to integrate with PicoD for JWT token generation\n490: - AR-011 (Router JWT 认证与签发) - Router JWT implementation for PicoD integration\n491: - Production deployment with JWT authentication enabled\n492: \n493: ### Notes\n494: - PicoD uses RS256 signing algorithm for JWT authentication\n495: - Public key loaded from PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY environment variable\n496: - All /api/* endpoints require JWT authentication\n497: - /health endpoint is publicly accessible\n498: - Token expiration checked with 1-minute leeway\n499: - Body size limit (32MB) applied after authentication\n500: - Public key access is thread-safe with read-write mutex\n501: - Server fails to start if public key not configured (fail-fast)\n502: - Error messages are generic to avoid exposing sensitive information\n\n(End of file - total 502 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: S\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify AuthManager struct matches design specification\n- [ ] Verify AuthManager has publicKey *rsa.PublicKey field\n- [ ] Verify AuthManager has mutex sync.RWMutex field\n- [ ] Verify NewAuthManager() function exists with correct signature\n- [ ] Verify ValidateToken() method exists with correct signature\n- [ ] Verify no additional unintended fields or methods are present\n\n**Verification**: Review pkg/picod/auth.go structure against design.md line 181-192\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775861533335,"end":1775861533362}}}}
